Uralkali Agrees to Lend Belaruskali $1 Billion, Vedomosti Says

-- B y   I l y a   A r k h i p o v
-- 
2011-06-10T06:47:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/russia-s-uralkali-lends-belaruskali-1-billion-vedomosti-says.html
OAO  Uralkali (URKA) ,  Russia ’s largest
potash producer, agreed to lend Belarus’s Belaruskali $1 billion
for 18 months,  Vedomosti  reported, citing a person it didn’t
identify.  The loan is linked to future potash sales, the Moscow-based
newspaper said. Belarus President Alexander Lukashenko asked
Uralkali’s billionaire owner Suleiman Kerimov for the funds
during a meeting on June 8, according to Vedomosti.  Uralkali’s press office declined to comment when contacted
by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Arkhipov in Moscow at 
 iarkhipov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Brad Cook at 
 bcook7@bloomberg.net  